<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_EP21_ProjectGold_AlliancesAndRivalries" s="488450">
  <T n="category">488441<!--TutorialCategory: tutorial_Category_EP21_ProjectGold--></T>
  <T n="name">0x37365A92<!--String: "Alliances & Rivalries"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP21\UI\Tutorial\EP21_Lessons_Dynasty_AlliancesRivalries1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:efe5399add2d6c5d</T>
      <T n="text">0x5B736C57<!--String: "In order to expand their power and influence, or create drama, Dynasty Heads can choose to <b><font color='#199C2C'>forge Alliances and declare Rivalries</font></b> with each other.\n\nThese connections can impact the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Prestige</font></b> of both Dynasties as well as the way Members of each Dynasty interact with each other.\n\nAn <b><font color='#199C2C'>Alliance</font></b> may be harder to start and maintain, but has mainly positive effects, while a <b><font color='#199C2C'>Rivalry</font></b> is easier to start and uphold, but is more likely to spark negative consequences."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP21\UI\Tutorial\EP21_Lessons_Dynasty_AlliancesRivalries2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:efe5399add2d6c5e</T>
      <T n="text">0xD22B0B5C<!--String: "<b><font color='#199C2C'>Alliances</font></b> give a large boost to Prestige and encourage Members to foster positive relationships, granting increased success in friendly social interactions with each other. Forging an Alliance requires a higher friendship level between the Heads and Heirs of both Dynasties, and it is more difficult to maintain over time, but the payoff is likely to be worth the effort. However, beware, losing an Alliance will result in a loss of Prestige!\n\n<b><font color='#199C2C'>Rivalries</font></b> give a smaller boost to Prestige, but are easier to declare and maintain. Members of Rival Dynasties have a harder time building relationships with each other, and friendship (or romance) between Members of Rival Dynasties could even result in a <b><font color='#199C2C'>Scandal</font></b>. Rival Dynasty members will seek to cause trouble, and may even crash each others' parties, looking for a fight."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP21\UI\Tutorial\EP21_Lessons_Dynasty_AlliancesRivalries3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:efe5399add2d6c5f</T>
      <T n="text">0xD898CCC3<!--String: "It's not only the Members within a Dynasty who have opinions on its Values. Allies and Rivals care too!\n\nDynasties that have <b><font color='#199C2C'>conflicting Values</font></b> (the Values that can't be selected together) will tend to not get along. It will be easier to start a <b><font color='#199C2C'>Rivalry</font></b> between such Dynasties.\n\nValues can be <b><font color='#199C2C'>matching</font></b>, as well. For example, the Head of a Diplomatic Dynasty will be more likely to accept an <b><font color='#199C2C'>Alliance Proposal</font></b> from someone who is the Head of a Dynasty with the Diplomatic, Caring, or Charisma Value."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
  <L n="tags">
    <E>Lesson_EP21_ProjectGold_Dynasty</E>
  </L>
